Just last month, seven workers were killed at the mines Masakhane operation in Driefontein. JOHANNESBURG - The National Union of Mineworkers (NUM) has confirmed that a worker has died at Sibanye Stillwater's Driefontein Hlanganani shaft near Carletonville. It’s understood the mineworker was killed during a ground fall. Just last month, seven workers were killed at the mines Masakhane operation in Driefontein. The NUM's Peter Bailey says the latest fatality is concerning. “There was a health and safety indaba held between the top management and the union representatives, and just a couple of days later we have another fatality. This speaks volumes of the commitment and the dedication of the employer towards saving black lives in the mining industry,” he said. (Edited by Thapelo Lekabe)